A health worker drags an electrocardiograph at the Charlotte Maxeke Hospital in Johannesburg. PORT ELIZABETH - Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize has announced that South Africa's COVID-19 cases have increased to 3,465. There have been no new reported deaths from the coronavirus in the last 24 hours. The death toll from the virus remains at 58. There have been 126, 937 tests conducted in South Africa of which 5,427 were done in the last 24 hours. WATCH: 'Lockdown should not be extended but not withdrawn' - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.